@104394 = ~Sherwyn is a bard from Neverwinter, an adventurer and merrymaker. Her mother was an adventurer, who married a man of wealth after her daughter was born. Because of her spending too much money, the man lost his fortune and left his wife and daughter with only debts. In order not to give up the rich life to which she was already accustomed, Sherwyn's mother wanted to see her wed to a wealthy bachelor. But these plans were not to be, because Sherwyn fell in love with the poor bard and ran off with him. For several years they traveled together, and Sherwyn learned how to become a bard in her own right. She returned to Neverwinter only many years later to save her hometown from the plague. She found her mother has been living all these years as a poor seamstress and sufferng from bonerot. She blamed her daughter for the poor luck which had befallen her. Nevertheless, Sherwyn hopes to find a way to heal his mother and get on the path to reconciliation.~/*Vous avez fait la connaissance de Fenthick et Desther. Le premier est le conseiller d'Aribeth, mais aussi son fiancé, tandis que le second est un fidèle de Heaum venu aider à combattre l'épidémie et qui ne semble guère impressionné par les efforts déployés jusque-là. Fenthick vous a demandé de vous rendre au palais de justice de Padhiver afin que vous partiez en quête du remède contre l'épidémie de Mort Hurlante. Jai fui Padhiver avec Dannen, nous voyageâmes loin, et il mapprit tout lart des bardes. Je ne rentrai pas chez moi avant de longues années... il y a très peu de temps. Elle vécut depuis lors en pauvre couturière pleine d'amertume ; elle me reproche la malchance qui lui a tout fait perdre. M'aider ? Oui, employer le vieux pour trouver l'antique, le fou pour trouver l'affolant !*/
